# Plan of Care

## What this document is
A Plan of Care is a document that outlines the proposed care and arrangements for the child, including living arrangements, education, and any services needed.

## Why this document exists
It helps the court understand the plan for the child's well-being and how their needs will be met.

## How to fill it out
1. Include the child's details and current living situation.
2. Describe the proposed care arrangements and who will be responsible for each aspect.
3. Outline any educational plans, medical care, or other services needed.
4. Make sure the information is clear and accurate, as it will be reviewed by the court.

## Important note
This form is part of the official court process and should reflect the best interests of the child.
